    "completed": "False",
    "instruction": "Using the df_anom_summary (which contains one row per (cmdb_id,kpi_name) with count_high/count_low and earliest_anom_ts), aggregate by cmdb_id and produce a compact summary table (store as df_anom_by_component) with columns: cmdb_id, num_faulty_kpis (number of distinct kpi_name with >=1 anomaly), sum_count_high (sum of count_high across its KPIs), sum_count_low (sum of count_low), earliest_anom_ts (minimum earliest_anom_ts across its KPIs), latest_anom_ts (maximum earliest_anom_ts across its KPIs), max_severity_metric (the maximum of max_value_in_window/p95 ratio across its KPIs — calculate ratio only when p95 != 0, else set ratio to NaN), and example_top_kpi (the kpi_name of the KPI with highest (count_high+count_low) for that component). Return: (1) top 20 rows of df_anom_by_component sorted by num_faulty_kpis descending, limited columns as above; (2) total number of distinct components with >=1 faulty KPI; (3) list up to 10 components whose earliest_anom_ts is the earliest (chronologically) to help find distinct failure start times. Keep outputs compact."
}

